Description of included files
  lab0.c - This is the source code for the project. It's basic purpose is to copy stdin to stdout; it
    also includes some options such as --input, --output, --segfault, and --catch.
  Makefile - This contains settings for compilation. It includes default, clean, dist, and check.
  backtrace.png - This is a screenshot of a segmentation fault and its associated stack-trace.
  breakpoint.png - This is a screenshot of a breakpoint and variable inspection.
  README - This is the file you are currently reading. It includes a description of the files, 
    smoke-test cases, and resources used to complete this project.


Description of smoke-test cases
  # Test 1: Checking normal use of the function - can the standard input be copied to standard output properly?
    - Program should exit with code 0
  # Test 2: Checking for segfault with --segfault --catch option
    - Program should exit with code 4
  # Test 3: Checking what happens with an unrecognized argument
    - Program should exit with code 1
  # Test 4: Checking what happens when unable to open output file
    - Program should exit with code 3
  # Test 5: Checking what happens when unable to open input file
    - Program should exit with code 2


